-------
ENTROPY
-------

The entropy contributions are T*S = T*(S(el)+S(vib)+S(rot)+S(trans))
     S(el)   - electronic entropy
     S(vib)  - vibrational entropy
     S(rot)  - rotational entropy
     S(trans)- translational entropy
The entropies will be listed as multiplied by the temperature to get
units of energy

Electronic entropy                ...      0.00130891 Eh      0.82 kcal/mol
Vibrational entropy               ...      0.04345806 Eh     27.27 kcal/mol
Rotational entropy                ...      0.01665831 Eh     10.45 kcal/mol
Translational entropy             ...      0.02099883 Eh     13.18 kcal/mol
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Final entropy term                ...      0.08242412 Eh     51.72 kcal/mol

